      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA solvers (FDA in-house, Ansys Mechanical, DePuy Synthes proprietary) operate under documented software quality assurance plans including version control, regression testing, and change management procedures consistent with Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions were executed for each solver. Results for linear elastic beam bending and contact patch problems confirm code correctness within expected numerical tolerances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were performed for the pedicle screw and rod assembly. Peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod interface converged to within 3% between successive mesh refinements, satisfying the Gradation 2 threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals were monitored and confirmed to fall below 1e-6 for all load steps. Contact convergence was verified through force balance checks at each increment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Model setup and execution were performed by experienced analysts with documented training records. Independent cross-checks between the three modelling teams identified and resolved two minor boundary condition discrepancies prior to final analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum mechanics with frictional contact at the screw-rod interface was selected. The choice is justified by literature precedent for quasi-static ASTM F1717 loading and confirmed by sensitivity analyses showing negligible plasticity in the construct under the applied compression-bending moment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus 114 GPa, Poisson ratio 0.34) were sourced from ASTM F136 certificate-of-compliance data for the actual production lots. Geometric inputs were derived from CMM measurements of three representative constructs with reported uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative components were tested. Sample traceability to manufacturing lot records was confirmed. Dimensional inspection verified that all specimens fell within engineering drawing tolerances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single compressive preload level (100 N) per ASTM F1717. The absence of multiple preload conditions limits the ability to validate model behaviour across the physiological loading envelope. This factor falls one gradation below the required level and constitutes a known gap in the current validation evidence package."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions were mapped directly to the physical test fixture geometry. Actuator displacement control, load cell calibration records, and fixture compliance corrections were incorporated into the simulation input deck to ensure parametric equivalency."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness and peak rod bending moment at 6 mm actuator displacement were compared against experimental values using mean absolute percentage error (MAPE). All three FEA models achieved MAPE below 8% across the N=11 sample, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and rod bending moment are the primary regulatory quantities of interest for ASTM F1717 510(k) submissions. These QoIs are directly linked to clinical performance indicators for spinal stabilisation implants as referenced in FDA guidance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the stated model risk level.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity replicates the ASTM F1717 test configuration in geometry, loading mode, and material system. The validated FEA ensemble directly supports the intended submission claim regarding compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct."
    }
  ],
